Node.Notes: Literally "cannot find their hands," in the sense that in death their hands are useless to them.
Uncertain. Perhaps wrath of God's enemies turn into praise after their defeat or the rebellion of wrathful humanity enables God to display his power and glory, eliciting praise from his people.

Uncertain. Many render literally "with the remainder of wrath you gird yourself" with no attempt to explain meaning. Some suggest "the remainder of wrath" refers to those who survive God's anger. Others change the text in various ways.
Seems to refer to God as the one who causes humankind to fear him.
Apparently, "cuts off" (used of cutting off/gathering grapes in lv25:5, 11; dt24:21; ju9:27). Many go with a conjecture and translate "humbles."
